body:
# ESLint Rules

Rules are the core of ESLint — each rule validates a specific pattern and can report warnings or errors. Rules are identified by name (e.g., `no-unused-vars`, `eqeqeq`) and configured with a severity and optional options.

## Rule Severities

| Value | Meaning | Effect |
|-------|---------|--------|
| `"off"` or `0` | Disabled | Rule does not run |
| `"warn"` or `1` | Warning | Reports but exit code stays 0 |
| `"error"` or `2` | Error | Reports and exit code becomes 1 |

Use `"error"` for rules you want to enforce in CI. Use `"warn"` when introducing new rules or flagging non-critical issues.

## Configuring Rules in Config

```javascript
// eslint.config.mjs
import js from "@eslint/js";

export default [
  js.configs.recommended,
  {
    rules: {
      // Simple severity
      "no-console": "warn",
      eqeqeq: "error",

      // Severity with options
      "no-unused-vars": ["error", {
        argsIgnorePattern: "^_",
        varsIgnorePattern: "^_",
        caughtErrorsIgnorePattern: "^_",
      }],

      // Array form: [severity, ...options]
      "prefer-const": ["error", { ignoreReadBeforeAssign: true }],
      quotes: ["error", "double", { allowTemplateLiterals: true }],
      semi: ["error", "always"],
    },
  },
];
```

## Per-File Rule Overrides

Each config object in the array can target specific files:

```javascript
export default [
  // Default rules for all files
  {
    rules: {
      "no-console": "error",
      "no-debugger": "error",
    },
  },

  // Relax rules for test files
  {
    files: ["**/*.test.{js,ts}", "**/*.spec.{js,ts}", "tests/**"],
    rules: {
      "no-console": "off",
      "no-unused-expressions": "off",
      "@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any": "off",
    },
  },

  // Relax rules for scripts/tooling
  {
    files: ["scripts/**", "*.config.{js,ts}"],
    rules: {
      "no-console": "off",
    },
  },
];
```

## Inline Directives

### Disable for a Line

```javascript
// eslint-disable-next-line no-console
console.log("debug output");

console.log("debug"); // eslint-disable-line no-console
```

### Disable for a Block

```javascript
/* eslint-disable no-console */
console.log("start");
console.log("end");
/* eslint-enable no-console */
```

### Disable for Entire File

```javascript
/* eslint-disable no-console */
// Entire file ignores no-console
```

### Add Explanation (Best Practice)

```javascript
// eslint-disable-next-line no-console -- Intentional debug logging for staging
console.log("debug:", data);
```

## Recommended Rule Sets

```javascript
import js from "@eslint/js";

export default [
  // ESLint recommended (~50 rules)
  js.configs.recommended,

  // Override specific recommended rules
  {
    rules: {
      "no-unused-vars": ["error", { argsIgnorePattern: "^_" }],
    },
  },
];
```

## Common Rules Quick Reference

| Rule | Purpose | Fixable |
|------|---------|----------|
| `no-unused-vars` | Flag unused variables | No |
| `no-console` | Disallow console.log | No |
| `eqeqeq` | Require === over == | Yes |
| `prefer-const` | Use const when not reassigned | Yes |
| `no-var` | Disallow var | Yes |
| `semi` | Require/disallow semicolons | Yes |
| `quotes` | Enforce quote style | Yes |
| `no-debugger` | Disallow debugger | No |
| `no-undef` | Flag undeclared variables | No |
| `curly` | Require braces for blocks | Yes |
| `no-duplicate-imports` | No duplicate import paths | No |

## Reporting Unused Directives

Catch stale `eslint-disable` comments:

```javascript
export default [
  {
    linterOptions: {
      reportUnusedDisableDirectives: "error",
      reportUnusedInlineConfigs: "error",
    },
  },
];
```

Or via CLI:

```bash
npx eslint --report-unused-disable-directives .
```

## Plugin Rules

Plugin rules use namespaced names:

```javascript
import tseslint from "typescript-eslint";

export default [
  {
    rules: {
      // Plugin rules: "namespace/rule-name"
      "@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars": "error",
      "@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any": "warn",
      "react/prop-types": "off",
      "react-hooks/exhaustive-deps": "warn",
      "import/order": ["error", { "newlines-between": "always" }],
    },
  },
];
```

## Finding Rule Documentation

```bash
# Open rule docs in browser
npx eslint --print-config src/index.js | jq '.rules'

# Rule docs URL pattern
# https://eslint.org/docs/latest/rules/<rule-name>
# https://typescript-eslint.io/rules/<rule-name>
```
